ements.\nWhirlpool India faces competition from LG, Samsung, and stricter regulations; its shares fell 47% this year.","summary":"Advent's $1B deal to acquire a 31% stake in Whirlpool India collapsed due to valuation disagreements.\nWhirlpool India faces competition from LG, Samsung, and stricter regulations; its shares fell 47% this year.","url":"https://www.cnbctv18.com/market/stocks/exclusive-advents-1-billion-deal-talks-for-whirlpool-india-share-price-stake-collapse-sources-say-19783274.htm","imageUrl":null,"pubDate":"2025-12-06T18:32:37","source":"CNBC TV 18"},{"id":"398956","title":"Promoter stakes in Indian firms like IndiGo, Vedanta, and Whirlpool are falling, hitting an 8-year low by 2025. Reasons include debt repayment, high stock prices, SEBI's MPS rule, and personal diversification.\nInvestors should monitor promoter actions, FII/DII buying, and block deals via tools like Finology Ticker. Don't panic; assess reasons, buyers, and remaining stakes before reacting.","summary":"Promoter stakes in Indian firms like IndiGo, Vedanta, and Whirlpool are falling, hitting an 8-year low by 2025. Reasons include debt repayment, high stock prices, SEBI's MPS rule, and personal diversification.\nInvestors should monitor promoter actions, FII/DII buying, and block deals via tools like Finology Ticker. Don't panic; assess reasons, buyers, and remaining stakes before reacting.","url":"https://www.livemint.com/market/stock-market-news/why-promoter-stakes-are-falling-in-indian-stocks-and-what-investors-should-track-11764750974830.html","imageUrl":null,"pubDate":"2025-12-03T16:41:58","source":"Livemint"}]}]